# S03-T01: Radar Engine

## Objective
Port `drone-interface/6/src/components/Radar.vue` (Canvas 2D, 187 lines) to a React 19 component using priority-based RenderScheduler.

## Acceptance Criteria
- `src/features/hud/radar/Radar.tsx` renders to `<canvas>` with DPI scaling.
- Features: rotating sweep, concentric rings, crosshair center, fading blip history (trail), trajectory vectors.
- Subscribes to `RenderScheduler.CRITICAL` priority.
- Blips driven by `useTelemetryStore.targets` (read-only).
- Resize observer redraws on container size change.

## Steps
1. Create `RadarEngine` class (pure Canvas drawing, no React).
2. Wrap with `<Radar>` React component (mount/unmount lifecycle only).
3. Apply UI_REGULATION colors (cyan primary, pink for OPEN targets).
4. Implement trail fade using alpha compositing.

## Invariants
- React renders Canvas exactly once; all updates via imperative draw calls.
- No spring/elastic motion (per UI_REGULATION).
- Sweep is continuous, semi-transparent — no flashy neon.
